    <abstract>Hu Xinli reconstructs the inscriptions at Mount Jian according to the epigraphical
        studies by Ruan Yuan, Li Zuoxian, Sun Baotian, Qian Tai, and the rubbings kept in the museum
        of the city of Tai’an. For each of his 12 inscriptions he gives the measurements of the
        according rubbings.</abstract>
